[4] Cholera - India (Jalpaiguri)
Date: Sun, 6 Jun 2004
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@ntlworld.com>
Source: The Hindustan Times [edited]
<http://www.hindustantimes.com/news/181_808169,000900030001.htm>

At least 7 persons, including 3 minors, have died of cholera and 25
others are affected at Hantapara tea garden in Jalpaiguri district in the
past few days.
Health Department sources said the main water supply tank of the tea
garden had not been renovated or cleaned for a long time, leading to
the outbreak of the disease.
--
Pablo Nart
<p.nart@ntlworld.com>
